RL0 completions.dat metadata
============================

Path
----
data/rl0/completions.dat

Record layout
-------------
Each record is multi-line and begins with a numbered delimiter:

---[N]---
valence:<int>
tile_count:<int>
center:(v,x,y)
canonical_boundary:<poly>
tiles:<tile_list>
hidden:<coord_list>
indices:<int_list>

Fields
------
1) valence
   Single valence number for the completed target vertex.
   For tetrille this is one of {3,4,6}.

2) tile_count
   Number of tiles in this record, including the seed tile.

3) center
   Target vertex coordinate used for the completion.

4) canonical_boundary
   Canonical merged completion boundary.
   Poly format:
   [cycle0|cycle1|...]
   Cycle format:
   [(v,x,y),(v,x,y),...]

5) tiles
   Aligned tile cycles used by the completion.
   The first tile is the seed tile; remaining tiles are attachments.
   List format:
   [tile_cycle0,tile_cycle1,...]

6) hidden
   Hidden vertex set tracked for this completion state.
   List format:
   [(v,x,y),(v,x,y),...]

7) indices
   One integer per tile in `tiles`.
   Each integer is the vertex index in that aligned tile cycle whose
   coordinate equals the completed target vertex.

Canonicalization rules
----------------------
- The boundary is canonicalized over lattice symmetries.
- The same selected transform and translation are applied to `tiles`.
- `indices` remain aligned with `tiles` order.

Notes
-----
- Data contains only live-boundary completions for reuse by later
  runlevels.
- There is no CSV header row.
- Record delimiter lines make streaming and chunk parsing easier.
